To make your repo into a GitHub Pages site, you have two main options:

Option 1: Use GitHub Pages (Direct & Simple)

You can host the repo as a website directly from GitHubno Cloudflare needed unless you want custom domain control.

Steps:

  1. Go to your repo:
    https://github.com/OmniversalMediaLLC/OmniversalOverride

  2. Click Settings Scroll to "Pages" on the left sidebar (or go directly to https://github.com/OmniversalMediaLLC/OmniversalOverride/settings/pages)

  3. Under "Build and deployment":

    • Source: Choose main branch
    • Folder: Choose / (root) or /docs depending on your structure
    • Click Save

  4. GitHub will generate a URL like:
    https://omniversalmediallc.github.io/OmniversalOverride

  5. Wait a few minutesit takes time to build the site.

  6. (Optional) Add a README.md or index.html at root to serve as your home page.

Option 2: Use Cloudflare Pages (If You Want a Custom Domain or More Control)

Use Cloudflare if you're already managing your domain there and want enhanced speed, security, or build automation.

Steps:

  1. Log into Cloudflare Pages

  2. Connect your GitHub repo OmniversalOverride

  3. Choose your build settings (for a basic static site, often no build command is needed)

  4. Deploy and map a domain (e.g., override.omniversal.media)

Bonus Tips:

  • If you use index.md or index.html in the root, GitHub Pages will serve it.
  • You can use a static site generator like Jekyll or Hugo if desired, but it's optional.
